d01a1d75-c419-44fa-a7f1-3d537bf819ca	https://ideam.ie	IDEAM Research Institute | IDEAM	Tuition WaiverFee Waiver Valued at €5,500. Bachelor’s, Master’s degree or PhD students and graduates, or industry professionals with experience in a related area.– Must be a passport holder from an EU Member State or one of the following associated countries: Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, EEA countries (Iceland, Norway, Liechtenstein), Kosovo, Moldova, Montenegro, North Macedonia, Serbia, Türkiye, or Ukraine.– Requires certified evidence of English skills (unless a native speaker), specifically: IELTS score of 6.5TOEFL iBT score of 90. Tuition WaiverFee Waiver Valued at €5,500. Successful applicants will be eligible for a fee-waiver and a partial stipend of €1,000 per month, for eighteen (18) months or up until the end of the DigiWind project in December 2027. It is envisaged that up to five scholarships will be awarded. The successful candidates will be based at the TUS Campus in Limerick, Ireland studying in-person with access to online classes. Tuition WaiverFee Waiver Valued at €5,500. A recognised master’s qualification based on advanced, completed research.– In-demand skills, based on industry-based input.– A recognised qualification to enhance your future career.– A foundation for technical and scientific excellence, with opportunities to publish your work.– Potential future PhD studies. Tuition WaiverFee Waiver Valued at €5,500. The Irish Design Engineering and Advanced Manufacturing (IDEAM) Research Institute, led by Dr John Cosgrove, is focused on the research and development of data-driven solutions for Industry. With core expertise in Engineering, Energy, Electronics, Informatics and Manufacturing, IDEAM is a comprehensive, multi-disciplinary institute focused on the development of excellence in research, collaborative research projects and regional training & skills that can deliver impactful research and innovation.The Research Institute has an extensive industry support base across Ireland, is currently collaborating on 24 industry-based research projects, and is directly supported by a strong ecosystem of 65 actively engaged companies who have contributed to the definition and growth of this research area. Discover why leading researchers and industry partners choose IDEAM Research Institute to advance innovation - from groundbreaking studies to global impact. The IDEAM Research Institute proudly showcases its impact through measurable achievements. With over €15 million in annual research funding, we drive transformative advancements in science and technology. Our 150+ impactful projects span diverse fields, collaborating with over 100 trusted industry partners and leading researchers.Through 65+ high-quality publications in renowned journals and conferences, we ensure our research contributes to global innovation and knowledge-sharing. Explore how our collaborative efforts and cutting-edge initiatives are shaping the future across industries. IDEAM Research Institute Supports. Innovating for a better future. IDEAM Research Institute Supports. Empowering the next generation. IDEAM Research Institute Supports. Expert guidance for your challenges. IDEAM Research Institute Supports. Supporting innovation and research. IDEAM Research Institute Supports. IDEAM Institute pioneers innovative research in science and technology. We collaborate with academic, industry, and government partners to develop groundbreaking solutions, led by our dedicated multidisciplinary teams. IDEAM Research Institute Supports. We offer PhD, Masters, and Certificate programs to cultivate future professionals. Our hands-on workshops, seminars, and apprenticeships provide real-world experience and expert knowledge sharing.	[0.006821766,-0.024570955,0.027086925,0.011057834,-0.012269915,0.008505449,-0.082279555,0.00034280043,0.030791426,0.018850647,-0.026860427,-0.11760745,-0.029204356,0.03963632,-0.02618293,-0.039328825,-0.041165177,-0.0989723,-0.0176789